t speech.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3206, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"organising chief\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3205}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"a triumphalist speech\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the Games had transformed \\\"a nation of implacable complainers\\\" into \\\"unbridled supporters who do not want to stop singing\\\".\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3284}, {\"ngram\": \"a nation\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3310}, {\"ngram\": \"implacable complainers\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3336}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"unbridled supporters\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:Fibre optic cables targeted in new infrastructure attack in France Much of the media commentary has focused on the uplifting impact of the Games on the generally morose national mood.\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3470, \"end\": 3476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fibre optic cables\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3428}, {\"ngram\": \"new infrastructure attack\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"Much\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3481}, {\"ngram\": \"the media commentary\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3505}, {\"ngram\": \"the uplifting impact\", \"from\": 3521, \"to\": 3541}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"the generally morose national mood\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just weeks before the Olympics, snap elections called by President Emmanuel Macron delivered a hung parliament and a historic number of seats for the far-right National Rally party.\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3663, \"end\": 3678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3756, \"end\": 3770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"snap elections\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"a hung parliament\", \"from\": 3689, \"to\": 3706}, {\"ngram\": \"a historic number\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"seats\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Paris Games offered the capital and the entire country more than two weeks of fervour and happiness that were so unexpected and appreciated given that they came after a political period dominated by the sad passions of decline and xenophobia,\\\" said an editorial in Le Monde newspaper.\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 4068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Monde\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Games\", \"from\": 3780, \"to\": 3795}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3815}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire country\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3838}, {\"ngram\": \"more than two weeks\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3858}, {\"ngram\": \"fervour\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 3869}, {\"ngram\": \"happiness\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3883}, {\"ngram\": \"a political period\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3969}, {\"ngram\": \"the sad passions\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"decline\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4010}, {\"ngram\": \"xenophobia\", \"from\": 4015, \"to\": 4025}, {\"ngram\": \"an editorial\", \"from\": 4033, \"to\": 4045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For 17 days the stereotype of the indifferent, grumpy Frenchman went missing,\\\" wrote sports writer Owen Slot in The Times newspaper, adding that Paris had \\\"made the Olympic Games look more beautiful than ever before.\\\"\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4170, \"end\": 4179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\", \"score\": 0.9999870806357289, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Owen Slot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\"}, {\"begin\": 4183, \"end\": 4192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.999999999577085, \"rank\": 4.232760644644753e-10, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_ph