e LA Games\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4375}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flag\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:SA's Olympic medal hopes ratcheting up The ceremony followed 17 days of drama-filled sporting action lit up by Biles, American sprinter Noah Lyles, Pakistan's javelin king Arshad Nadeem and casual Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec, who has become an Internet sensation.\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4512, \"end\": 4514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999992701926138, \"rank\": 7.298072097396993e-07, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 4661, \"end\": 4669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999971314537, \"rank\": 2.8685087022984343e-09, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4710, \"end\": 4717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9212042580675258, \"rank\": 0.07730128253291356, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 4726, \"end\": 4731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.752702587691065e-13, \"text\": \"Yusuf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4563}, {\"ngram\": \"17 days\", \"from\": 4573, \"to\": 4580}, {\"ngram\": \"drama-filled sporting action\", \"from\": 4584, \"to\": 4612}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4628}, {\"ngram\": \"Arshad Nadeem\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4697}, {\"ngram\": \"an Internet sensation\", \"from\": 4753, \"to\": 4774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also featured a damaging gender row about two female boxers, Imane Khelif of Algeria and Taiwan's Lin Yu-ting, who both went on to win gold.\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4844, \"end\": 4856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 4860, \"end\": 4867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999994861355, \"rank\": 5.098278924772235e-10, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 4872, \"end\": 4878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999900837793, \"rank\": 7.082733492044968e-09, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 4881, \"end\": 4892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a damaging gender row\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4818}, {\"ngram\": \"two female boxers\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 4842}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 4918, \"to\": 4922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last day of sporting action saw the United States pip China for top spot in the battle for medals after the US women's basketball team squeezed past France 67-66 to clinch the last gold of the Games.\", \"from\": 4925, \"to\": 5128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4965, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9991580726615936, \"rank\": 0.0008425877188872648, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4983, \"end\": 4988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999998584207888, \"rank\": 1.046022257187119e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 5037, \"end\": 5039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9942813723361207, \"rank\": 0.00533629415764899, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5078, \"end\": 5084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The last day\", \"from\": 4925, \"to\": 4937}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting action\", \"from\": 4941, \"to\": 4956}, {\"ngram\": \"top spot\", \"from\": 4993, \"to\": 5001}, {\"ngram\": \"the battle\", \"from\": 5005, \"to\": 5015}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5026}, {\"ngram\": \"the last gold\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5114}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5118, \"to\": 5127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The win - the eighth consecutive Olympic women's basketball title won by the USA - ensured the Americans finished level with China on 40 golds each.\", \"from\": 5130, \"to\": 5278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5207, \"end\": 5210, \"